<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bashful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bashful,</orth> shamefaced: <cit><quote>he burns with b. shame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 49" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and forth with b. innocence doth hie,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1341" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1341</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>hence, b. cunning,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 81</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. sincerity and comely love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 55</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. modesty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 49</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you virtuous ass, you b. fool,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wherefore should you be so b.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 75</bibl></cit> (Fluellen says <emph>pashful</emph>). <cit><quote>and b. Henry deposed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 41</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her b. years,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.326" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 326</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>